polars-text is a Rust/PyO3 plugin for Polars providing tokenization,
concordance, quotation extraction, token-frequency, topic modelling
embedders, and related text-analytics expressions.

Developed by Sydney Informatics Hub (SIH), The University of Sydney,
for the Language Data Commons of Australia (LDaCA,
https://www.ldaca.edu.au) — a national research infrastructure project
funded by the Australian Research Data Commons (ARDC) and enabled by
the National Collaborative Research Infrastructure Strategy (NCRIS).

polars-text is developed primarily as a core component of LDaCA
Wordflow
(https://github.com/Australian-Text-Analytics-Platform/ldaca-wordflow),
but is designed to be used independently in research pipelines,
Jupyter notebooks, and other Polars-based data analyses.

If you use polars-text in research, please cite the Language Data
Commons of Australia (LDaCA) — see https://www.ldaca.edu.au for the
recommended citation form.
